# Homelab Network IP & VLAN Plan

## Overview
This document defines the current IP addressing scheme and VLAN segmentation for the homelab environment. The goal is to maintain clear separation between network zones while enabling controlled communication via firewall rules.

---

## VLAN & Subnet Allocation

| VLAN Name   | Subnet              | Gateway           | Purpose |
|------------|--------------------|-------------------|--------|
| MGMT       | 192.168.99.0/24    | 192.168.99.1      | Admin systems (primary + backup admin machines) |
| SERVERS    | 192.168.60.0/24    | 192.168.60.1      | Core infrastructure (AD, Splunk, NAS) |
| TEST       | 192.168.20.0/24    | 192.168.20.1      | Test PC / controlled lab environment |
| SANDBOX    | 192.168.50.0/24    | 192.168.50.1      | Malware testing / isolated environment |
| HOME       | 192.168.30.0/24    | 192.168.30.1      | Personal + family devices |
| IOT        | 192.168.40.0/24    | 192.168.40.1      | Smart devices / IoT router |
| WAN        | 10.0.0.0/24        | 10.0.0.1          | Upstream ISP network |

